llooggmmssgg -- System Administration

Hold COHERENT Login Message
/eettcc/llooggmmssgg

The file /eettcc/llooggmmssgg holds the message that COHERENT displays to prompt the
user to log  in.  The superuser bbiinn can use  eedd or MicroEMACS to change the
message to whatever she prefers.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
AAddmmiinniisstteerriinngg CCOOHHEERREENNTT

_N_o_t_e_s
The default message consists of the bell character <ccttrrll-GG> followed by the
text CCoohheerreenntt  llooggiinn:. If the  bell annoys you, simply  delete the <ccttrrll-GG>
from /eettcc/llooggmmssgg.
